re is an extensive amount of nepotism at this firm although it's to be expected at many firms of this size. The people running the sales team at this institution are unorganized, have little clear direction. There was a big cultural divide with the sales team treated as "overhead" while the PMs were put on a pedestal. Promises of big upsides are the carrot used by management but the products are rather difficult to push as they are very non-traditional and do not easily fit the retail Morningstar model. It would be difficult to recommend Tocqueville to professionals legitimately interested in financial sales.Advice to ManagementMore buy-in with respect to the sales effort. Fix the culture. Recognize that the products are unique and thus more difficult to close.Share on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (0) Tocqueville Asset Management Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Tocqueville Asset Management 2015-10-18 15:04 PDT Sep 16, 2015"Just want some access to Glass Door"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Analyst in New York, NYCurrent Employee - Analyst in New York, NYNeutral OutlookI have been working at Tocqueville Asset Management full-time (More than 5 years)Prosnice people flexible schedule for meConstoo many mouths to feedAdvice to Managementbring back sodas to the fridgeShare on FacebookShare on TwitterShare on WhatsAppShare via EmailCopy LinkLink Copied!Flag as InappropriateFlag as InappropriateHelpful (0) Tocqueville Asset Management Response seconds agoEdit • Delete Tocqueville Asset Management 2015-09-16 11:27 PDT Jun 5, 2015"Good firm"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementFormer Employee - Anonymous EmployeeFormer Employee - Anonymous EmployeeRecommendsPositive OutlookProsRwk is generous and smart CEOConsNothing I 